<doc id="1296177" wikidata="Q3777630" url="?curid=1296177" title="Carrickbanagher">
<text>Carrickbanagher ( or &quot;Carraig Beannchar&quot; meaning &quot;rock of the points&quot;) is a townland in County Sligo, Ireland between the towns of Collooney and Ballymote.

Carrickbanagher has an area of approximately , and had a population of 121 people as of the 2011 census.

